                            <comment id="16425354" author="pascalschumacher" created="Wed, 4 Apr 2018 11:23:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as I know neither commons-lang3 nor commons-text never supported SQL escaping. Commons-lang 2.x supported SQL escaping, but this was dropped in 3.0, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/article3_0.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/article3_0.html&lt;/a&gt; for details.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not aware of any other Java ASF project is providing this functionally, but there are a lot of projects so I may miss something.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have removed the mention of SQL escaping from the commons-text userguide.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
